  "body": "- [X] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue: see https://gitter.im/ConsenSys/truffle?at=60104755ac653a0802e352d9\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nimporting `@truffle/contract` results in a very large bundle size as it drags unnecessary packages for a production build. \r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Add a dependency on truffle/contract in your code `require(\"@truffle/contract\");` \r\n2. Create a build of your project\r\n3. Analyze your build with [source-map-explorer](https://www.npmjs.com/package/source-map-explorer)\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nTruffle should provide a way to create an optimized build that would result in a smaller, more optimized, bundle size.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nRight now, if you happen to require(\"@truffle/contract\"); in your code, you'll drag a LOT of things, many of which might not be necessary at all and bloats the resulting bundle. Here's for example the result I get if I yarn analyze our code using source-map-explore :point_down:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/197119/105915078-455cb400-5ffd-11eb-8930-11c3685b0b0b.png)\r\n\r\nThis doesn't seem optimized for a production build. I doubt for example that dragging highlight.js is useful in a production build.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Ubuntu 20.10\r\n* Ethereum client: -\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): truffle/contract 4.3.5\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v12.19.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.14.8\r\n",
